JaguarDB Software Integrity Warranty

The developers of JaguarDB hereby warrant and affirm that:

1. No Malware: The JaguarDB software does not contain any form of malware, spyware, trojans, 
worms, or any other malicious or harmful code designed to damage, disrupt, or compromise the user's system or data.

2. No Backdoors: JaguarDB includes no hidden functionality or backdoors that allow unauthorized 
remote access, external control, or surveillance of the user's environment.

3. No Malicious Intent: The software has been developed in good faith with no malicious logic or behavior, 
including but not limited to data theft, manipulation, or disruption of third-party systems.

4. No Ransomware or Extortion Mechanisms: JaguarDB does not and will never contain ransomware features, 
encryption-locking mechanisms, or code designed to extort users in exchange for access or functionality.

5. Source Integrity: All code has been developed internally or sourced from reputable, auditable open-source 
libraries. Best practices for code review and security hygiene have been followed during development.


